node.text: We get so many questions on how we’ve gotten all of our kids to sleep through the night! So today I wanted to sit down with @thekatiesittersclub and have her share what she's taught us that's changed our lives! It may not happen overnight, so don’t get discouraged, but I promise it will be so worth it if you implement these steps into your routines and stay CONSISTENT. Save this video to save yourself sleepless nights & to get the exact sleep schedules we use!

node.title: Steps & Sleep Schedules to get your infant sleeping through the night

Today @jessicadiamondrdn and I are chatting about desserts & leftover Halloween candy and a couple easy ways that kids can learn how to have a positive relationship with desserts. 

Knowing how to navigate kids + candy + desserts in a healthy neutral & fun way was something Tyler and I always wanted, but wasn’t sure exactly how to do it until we met our nutritionist @jessicadiamondrdn

Thought I’d share because I love her and her balanced, realistic philosophies on kids and desserts, feeding, nutrition ... (and basically everything!). Listen to learn more and we’ll have many more of these conversations and other resources coming soon!!

node.title: Why and how we came to believe in serving desserts with our kids' meals

node.text: Mothers around the world need our support now more than ever. Over 800 women die everyday due to birth complications, and right now, new and expecting mothers are some of the most vulnerable during the #Covid19 crisis. That is why I am honored to stand in solidarity with @mrsadriennebosh and @everymomcounts . This incredible organization supports mothers around the world by providing the resources and care necessary for a safe and healthy pregnancy. Join me in our mission by donating or spreading awareness about the ongoing maternal health crisis and to protect mothers during COVID-19. If you are able, I encourage you to make a donation, especially in honor of #GivingTuesday and International Day of the #Midwife tomorrow. A small gift makes a BIG impact. Donation link is in my bio. #ABxEMC #MaternalHealth #EMCLive

node.text:
Tyler and I had the best time sitting down with our friends Caroline and Michael Hobby talking about marriage, parenting, the importance of God in our lives, and sharing how we’re learning to navigate life with our new normal. We could have talked all day about this. Click link in my Bio to listen 🎙

Repost...
“We start this conversation with discussing the importance of learning each other’s love languages. Then Tyler tells his love story with Hayley and lets us know who initiated the first kiss ;). We talk secrets for making time for each other in the midst of busy music careers, Tyler being in Florida Georgia Line and Michael in A Thousand Horses. We also dive into parenting and how guys view it verses women, plus how we work together. Hayley and I share how essential our mama tribe is and what we share and learn from each other. We discuss why finding time for ourselves is as crucial as date nights with our spouse. We also talk about God and the importance of weaving him into every aspect of our lives and why we shouldn’t be scared of failing. This convo is as real as it gets!”

node.text:
Sweet summer family nights are my favorite as we’re back to our busy schedule. It makes these nights all the more special - right at home in our backyard! #BushsBeansPartner “Burger Night” is Liv’s favorite night of the week! We love having the whole spread of summer favorites, including @bushsbeans Baked Beans as the perfect pairing with our burgers! So easy to cook and serve - and a favorite of Luca’s for sure! We love that something so simple in our own little backyard oasis is what makes the most special summer memories. 
 
@bushsbeans is hosting a Bush’s Beautiful Summer Contest where a lucky fan will win a bean-inspired backyard of their dreams designed by HGTV’s “Good Bones” star Mina Starsiak Hawk! For details on how to enter, go to http://bushbeans.com/beautifulsummer - the contest is open now through July 18th! #BushsBeautifulSummerContest
